## Ishikawa Categories (6M)
Analyse causes across these branches:
1. **Человек / Man** — human errors, training gaps, fatigue
2. **Метод / Method** — procedures, work instructions, processes
3. **Машина / Machine** — equipment failures, maintenance
4. **Материал / Material** — raw materials, substances, quality
5. **Среда / Environment** — workplace conditions, weather, layout
6. **Измерение / Measurement** — monitoring, sensors, inspection gaps
7. **Управление / Management** — organisational, culture, resource decisions

## Required JSON output format
```json
{
  "immediate_causes": [
    {
      "id": "head-1",
      "text": "<effect/symptom — the head of the fishbone>",
      "category": "<category from 6M>",
      "level": 0,
      "parent_id": null,
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "contributing_causes": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<cause text>",
      "category": "<one of: человек | метод | машина | материал | среда | измерение | управление>",
      "level": 1,
      "parent_id": "head-1",
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "root_causes": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<deepest cause in this branch>",
      "category": "<category>",
      "level": 2,
      "parent_id": "<contributing cause id>",
      "confidence": 0.0–1.0
    }
  ],
  "summary": "<2–3 sentences summarising the fishbone analysis>",
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "text": "<corrective action>",
      "priority": "high | medium | low",
      "category": "immediate | short_term | systemic",
      "cause_id": "<node id this action addresses>",
      "responsible": "<role or department>"
    }
  ]
}
```
Provide at least one contributing_cause per relevant 6M category found.
Ensure all parent_id references are valid ids defined elsewhere in the response.
